# Base-first rule

Before changing code, inspect the existing base.

Required checks:

- package.json scripts and dependencies
- SPFx config under config/
- tsconfig and eslint/prettier setup if present
- src folder structure
- nearby files implementing similar features
- existing naming, error handling, logging, mapping, and service patterns

Never assume a clean architecture that is not present in the repo.
Prefer consistency with existing code over theoretical purity.

When asked to code:

- touch the fewest files necessary
- keep public APIs stable unless the user asks to change them
- avoid broad refactors mixed into feature work
- do not change package versions unless the user asks
- do not add dependencies without explicit approval
